sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A Composite BioScaffold Part (PpiI and PsrI) for Protein Fusions (see Design Page)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Brings together a BioScaffold part that removes protein tails with one that removes protein heads in order to create a BioScaffold part that can help create protein fusions using standard assembly
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part that links the two BioScaffold parts can be altered as desired--here I just wanted to leave at least 7 bp beyond the internal scars.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Linker for BioScaffold Parts, example of Gamma BioScaffold part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Will use as a linker when fusing two BioScaffold parts, can be created as an oligo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: needs to be longer than 28 bp

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A BioScaffold Part (Uses PpiI), Protein Tail Remover see Part Design Page
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: When placed in a BioBrick assembly and cut with the restriction enzyme PpiI, this part will direct the restriction enzymes to cut outside the BioBrick scar still in testing, uses restriction enzyme sites PpiI (2) PacI (2) MabI (2), will place in pSB1AK3 vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Can be used to removed protein tails for protein fusions, see BBF RFC 15
